The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Calcutta Tramways Company will introduce 70 new buses on Monday. Officials said the buses will ply on various routes. Transport minister Subash Chakraborty will flag off the vehicles at Esplanade. 

 The first cyber cafe at Howrah station was inaugurated on Friday by S.S. Khurana, general manager, Eastern Railway. The cafe will offer facilities like high-speed Internet browsing, emailing, audio-video chatting through web cams and Internet telephony.

 Three men were arrested in Khatir Bazar, in Barrackpore, on the northern fringes of the city, late on Thursday for carrying arms illegally. Police said the arrests followed a clash between two groups.

 Joydeb Halder, 45, was run over by a bus on Diamond Harbour Road on Friday evening. Police said Halder was trying to board the bus. He was taken to a local hospital, where he died. The driver and conductor of the bus have been arrested.

 A 45-year-old CPM supporter, Shakti Mondal, was shot dead in Baruipur on Friday. Police said Mondal was on his way home when four men attacked him. He was taken to a local hospital, where he was declared dead.

 Asgar Ali, 22, a resident of Kaliachak, in Malda, was found dead in a train compartment at Howrah station on Friday morning. Police said Asgar, who was returning home from Mumbai, might have died of jaundice.

